body.description: Incorporate understated modern style into your work or living space with the Humble Crew Plastic Desk Chair with Metal Frame. Its sleek, industrial design features a durable metal frame with a plastic square seat and back. This compact office chair is perfect for use at your home office desk or in the kitchen, blending in effortlessly for a fresh and classic aesthetic. Lightweight and stackable, it is easy to store when not in use. This armless chair with no wheels also adds a polished look to teen bedrooms, makeup vanities or dorm rooms. With a slim and narrow yet sturdy construction, it is the perfect small-space living solution for any room requiring additional seating. It is easy to assemble with all hardware included. Simply wipe clean for a long lasting, contemporary look in whatever room you choose. Each chair has a maximum 200 lb. weight limit and is sold separately. This chair is available in white, black, grey, navy blue, and red to seamlessly suit any home's style. No cushion included. Light daily usage recommended. Product Sizing— Assembled Chair Dimensions: 16"W x 19"D x 30"H Seat Height: 18" Item weight: 6 lbs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Easy to put together, just a little hard to get the seat onto the chair you have to really push lol. But the chair is great, comfortable and lightweight and matches the rest of my furniture.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 9, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Worst Chair Ever! Don't waste your money, time, and hope on this.
reviews.reviewText: First off, the package was delayed. However, I digress. When the package arrived, I was super excited to build it. I love building my furniture. I never had issues building things on my own. This product was the worst chair that I've ever seen.1 - The metal pieces were all rusted where the holes were and the ends of the metal pieces.2 - the manual/instructions were garbage. I literally sat in my living room, trying to understand this manual. It was like I was playing telestrations with this manual.3 - The pieces don't align. I've tried multiple ways in case I misinterpreted the manual. I even took their advice not to tighten the bolts until the final steps. The backrest didn't even fit. The chair legs were not flushed on the floor when they did fit. One leg would always be lifted (not touching the floor). The seat took some pressure to snap on. The screw meant to nail the backrest to the chair didn't fit. I could only screw 1/3of it into the chair hole. Then, it's bent in such a weird way that it was uncomfortable to sit in.4 - This product was $40+ after tax.Don't fall for this trap. I wish I could give it -5 stars.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 14, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Simple but not everyday use
reviews.reviewText: Not the easiest to put together as far as pieces lining up, and not the sturdiest piece. However we are just using this for a craft desk in a guest room so it fits our needs. Cute simplistic chair

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Perfect desk chair for my sons room, easy to put together

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 17, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The size is for someone 14 years old or under. Not very durable. Screws loosen quickly. The back moves repeatedly up and down. There is no screw to keep it in place. Very light weight.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It was a little difficult to assemble, but it was a good product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 7, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars DO NOT BUY
reviews.reviewText: I really wanted this chair, and when I received it, it had some rust damage. It was a few months before I decided to purchase it again, and I'm extremely disappointed that I have to return it yet again for the second time!! This time, the holes did not align with the nail. And while the product was picked up the next day, after I reported my return, I'm still waiting on my refund and it's been a week. It's extremely disappointing to have to go through the process yet again. it seemed like the perfect chair for the desk I bought with it initially, but I guess I was mistaken.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 15, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Came Rusty, Overpriced for Quality
reviews.reviewText: Product came rusty/dirty. Chair itself is quite unstable despite following the instructions. Back is pretty uncomfortable because of how small the curve is, and the screws won’t go all the way in like they should. Pretty disappointed especially for the price.
